quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  34,8,"Did he invent a lie about Allah or is there madnessin him? Rather, those who do not believe in the Hereafter are in punishment and extreme misguidance."
  34,9,"Have they not seen what lies before them and behind them of the heaven and the earth? If <span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Hamza, Al-Kesa’i and Khalaf read it as: “If He wills, He can…”</span>,footnotes:2:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: All except for Hafs read it as: “fragments”.</span>
  34,10,"And surely, We bestowed upon David grace from Us: “O mountains, echo with him(My praises) , and you birds(too) .” And We softened iron for him."